28/* !!ONLY FOR USE INTERNALLY TO LIBARCHIVE!! */
29
30/*
31 * This header is the first thing included in any of the libarchive
32 * source files. As far as possible, platform-specific issues should
33 * be dealt with here and not within individual source files. I'm
34 * actively trying to minimize #if blocks within the main source,
35 * since they obfuscate the code.
36 */
37
38#ifndef ARCHIVE_PLATFORM_H_INCLUDED
39#define ARCHIVE_PLATFORM_H_INCLUDED
40
41/* archive.h and archive_entry.h require this. */
42#define __LIBARCHIVE_BUILD 1
43
44#if defined(PLATFORM_CONFIG_H)
45/* Use hand-built config.h in environments that need it. */
46#include PLATFORM_CONFIG_H
47#elif defined(HAVE_CONFIG_H)
48/* Most POSIX platforms use the 'configure' script to build config.h */
49#include "config.h"
50#else
51/* Warn if the library hasn't been (automatically or manually) configured. */
52#error Oops: No config.h and no pre-built configuration in archive_platform.h.
53#endif
54
55/* It should be possible to get rid of this by extending the feature-test
56 * macros to cover Windows API functions, probably along with non-trivial
57 * refactoring of code to find structures that sit more cleanly on top of
58 * either Windows or Posix APIs. */
59#if (defined(__WIN32__) || defined(_WIN32) || defined(__WIN32)) && !defined(__CYGWIN__)
60#include "archive_windows.h"
61#endif
62
63/*
64 * The config files define a lot of feature macros. The following
65 * uses those macros to select/define replacements and include key
66 * headers as required.
67 */
68
69/* Get a real definition for __FBSDID or __RCSID if we can */
70#if HAVE_SYS_CDEFS_H
71#include <sys/cdefs.h>
72#endif
73
74/* If not, define them so as to avoid dangling semicolons. */
75#ifndef __FBSDID
76#define __FBSDID(a) struct _undefined_hack
77#endif
78#ifndef __RCSID
79#define __RCSID(a) struct _undefined_hack
80#endif
81
82/* Try to get standard C99-style integer type definitions. */
83#if HAVE_INTTYPES_H
84#include <inttypes.h>
85#endif
86#if HAVE_STDINT_H
87#include <stdint.h>
88#endif
89
90/* Borland warns about its own constants! */
91#if defined(__BORLANDC__)
92# if HAVE_DECL_UINT64_MAX
93# undef UINT64_MAX
94# undef HAVE_DECL_UINT64_MAX
95# endif
96# if HAVE_DECL_UINT64_MIN
97# undef UINT64_MIN
98# undef HAVE_DECL_UINT64_MIN
99# endif
100# if HAVE_DECL_INT64_MAX
101# undef INT64_MAX
102# undef HAVE_DECL_INT64_MAX
103# endif
104# if HAVE_DECL_INT64_MIN
105# undef INT64_MIN
106# undef HAVE_DECL_INT64_MIN
107# endif
108#endif
109
110/* Some platforms lack the standard *_MAX definitions. */
111#if !HAVE_DECL_SIZE_MAX
112#define SIZE_MAX (~(size_t)0)
113#endif
114#if !HAVE_DECL_SSIZE_MAX
115#define SSIZE_MAX ((ssize_t)(SIZE_MAX >> 1))
116#endif
117#if !HAVE_DECL_UINT32_MAX
118#define UINT32_MAX (~(uint32_t)0)
119#endif
120#if !HAVE_DECL_INT32_MAX
121#define INT32_MAX ((int32_t)(UINT32_MAX >> 1))
122#endif
123#if !HAVE_DECL_INT32_MIN
124#define INT32_MIN ((int32_t)(~INT32_MAX))
125#endif
126#if !HAVE_DECL_UINT64_MAX
127#define UINT64_MAX (~(uint64_t)0)
128#endif
129#if !HAVE_DECL_INT64_MAX
130#define INT64_MAX ((int64_t)(UINT64_MAX >> 1))
131#endif
132#if !HAVE_DECL_INT64_MIN
133#define INT64_MIN ((int64_t)(~INT64_MAX))
134#endif
135#if !HAVE_DECL_UINTMAX_MAX
136#define UINTMAX_MAX (~(uintmax_t)0)
137#endif
138#if !HAVE_DECL_INTMAX_MAX
139#define INTMAX_MAX ((intmax_t)(UINTMAX_MAX >> 1))
140#endif
141#if !HAVE_DECL_INTMAX_MIN
142#define INTMAX_MIN ((intmax_t)(~INTMAX_MAX))
143#endif
144
145/*
146 * If we can't restore metadata using a file descriptor, then
147 * for compatibility's sake, close files before trying to restore metadata.
148 */
149#if defined(HAVE_FCHMOD) || defined(HAVE_FUTIMES) || defined(HAVE_ACL_SET_FD) || defined(HAVE_ACL_SET_FD_NP) || defined(HAVE_FCHOWN)
150#define CAN_RESTORE_METADATA_FD
151#endif
152
153/*
154 * glibc 2.24 deprecates readdir_r
155 */
156#if defined(HAVE_READDIR_R) && (!defined(__GLIBC__) || !defined(__GLIBC_MINOR__) || __GLIBC__ < 2 || (__GLIBC__ == 2 && __GLIBC_MINOR__ < 24))
157#define USE_READDIR_R 1
158#else
159#undef USE_READDIR_R
160#endif
161
162/* Set up defaults for internal error codes. */
163#ifndef ARCHIVE_ERRNO_FILE_FORMAT
164#if HAVE_EFTYPE
165#define ARCHIVE_ERRNO_FILE_FORMAT EFTYPE
166#else
167#if HAVE_EILSEQ
168#define ARCHIVE_ERRNO_FILE_FORMAT EILSEQ
169#else
170#define ARCHIVE_ERRNO_FILE_FORMAT EINVAL
171#endif
172#endif
173#endif
174
175#ifndef ARCHIVE_ERRNO_PROGRAMMER
176#define ARCHIVE_ERRNO_PROGRAMMER EINVAL
177#endif
178
179#ifndef ARCHIVE_ERRNO_MISC
180#define ARCHIVE_ERRNO_MISC (-1)
181#endif
182
183#endif /* !ARCHIVE_PLATFORM_H_INCLUDED */
184
